Head (
Fig. 2C
). Occiput clearly swollen medially. Fronto-orbital plate with 5 to 6 pairs of proclinate frontal setae, lowermost frontal seta not reaching antennal insertion. Fronto-orbital plate and parafacial bare. Frontal vitta somewhat widened anteriorly. Facial ridge with 1 setula in lower third. Lower facial margin not protruding, invisible in profile. Gena height about 5.5 x eye height. Vibrissa long, inserted at level of lower facial margin. Five to 7 subvibrissal setae.

Abdomen (
Fig. 2A–B
). Syntergite I+II with mid-dorsal longitudinal depression extending to posterior margin. Sternites II to V absent (wholly membranous).
